 MBOMBELA –  Martin Jeffrey from Emer-G-Med was one of the first ones on the scene. “According to eyewitness reports the bakkie was traveling from Mbombela to Barberton while the taxi was traveling in the opposite direction. “The driver of the bakkie lost control and hit the side of the hill before it collided head on with the taxi,” Jeffrey confirmed. Photo: Martin Jeffrey The driver of the taxi was transported to Rob Ferreira by Emer-G-Med while the driver of the Hilux was transported to the same hospital by ER24. Both patients sustained only minor injuries. There is a stop-and-go for all drivers travelling on the R40 between Mbombela and Barberton. Read also: Protest leads to R37 closure 